name: Quick and Easy Fish Tacos
author: Chris
summary: You can serve these delightful tacos with a tossed salad and french fries, or just throw it all together for a quick and tasty snack.  If you use salsa and tartar sauce, you can make it ahead or use store-bought.
ingredients: ½ pound finely shredded red cabbage
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C)
Arrange fish sticks in a single layer on a baking sheet, and bake 20 minutes in the preheated oven, or until crisp and golden brown
Remove from heat and cut into thirds
Heat the vegetable oil in a skillet over medium-high heat
Fill the heated tortillas with fish stick portions, cabbage, tartar sauce, and salsa to serve
